    "To perform the evaluation, we record the peak virtual memory usage during constructionfoot_1.",
    "SPTAG-BKT and SPTAG-KDT demonstrate efficient memory utilization (1M and 25GB) despite having the highest indexing time.",
    "For larger datasets, ELPIS has the lowest indexing memory footprint, occupying up to 40% less memory than HNSW and 30% less than Vamana during indexing.",
    "This is because ELPIS needs a smaller maximum out-degree and beam width compared to its competitors.",
    "HNSW has a higher indexing memory footprint due to its use of a graph layout optimized for direct access to node edges through a large contiguous block allocation [1]."
  ],
